      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BENTLEY FISHER (2) is struggling to break through but racing consistently, finishing in the minors three starts on end. Last time out flew the lids with a fast early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when second (25.18) at Gunnedah over 431m. Has a strong record from box 2, including three wins. Must come into calculations. KING KERMARO (4) is a handy dog who jumped from box 3 last time out and scored by a nose at Maitland (22.72). Has a solid record from this box including three wins and a minor placing. Will go close again if runs up to latest. DREAM LINKIN (1) was safely held in tougher company last start after settling off pace at Bulli, but prior to that won by 0.8 lengths at Bulli (19.29) beating Ace Is Fire in a Grade 5 on June 2. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Better than last start and can bounce back. KAELIX NITRO (8) is a last-start placegetter with solid claims again.",
